type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

! `<$calc>` Cheatsheet

!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Values |!Default |!Description |
| `output` |`katex` · `text` |`katex` |Rendering backend |
| `show` |`result` · `formula` · `full` |`result` |What to display. `formula`/`full` degrade to `result` when body is a plain literal. |
| `mode` |`inline` · `block` |`inline` |Display mode. Katex: render mode. `output="text"`: centres result in a block `<div>`. |
| `locale` |`en` · `en-US` · `fr` · `fr-FR` · BCP-47 |`en` |Output number format. All locales use NNBSP (U+202F) as thousands separator. |
| `notation` |`auto` · `fixed` · `scientific` · `engineering` · `bin` · `oct` · `hex` |`auto` |Numeric output notation |
| `precision` |positive integer |6 |Display digits (decimal places or significant digits); ignored for bin/oct/hex |
| `calcPrec` |`float` · `64` · `128` · `256` |`float` |Arithmetic precision mode ⚠️ |
| `scope` |tiddler title or `{a:1, b:2}` |— |Variable scope |
| `silence` |`yes` · `no` |`no` |Suppress expression errors |

;`output` values:
* `katex` (default) — KaTeX when plugin installed, pretty-printed plain text fallback
* `text` — always pretty-printed plain text (π, ·, superscripts, √, ∛, !, log₂…)

;`show` values:
* `result` — evaluate and render the numeric result
* `formula` — typeset the expression without evaluating; `notation`, `precision`, `calcPrec`, `scope` are ignored. Degrades to `result` when the body is a plain numeric literal.
* `full` — `formula = result`. Same demotion applies.

;`notation` values:
* `auto` / `fixed` / `scientific` / `engineering` — locale-aware decimal output; `precision` controls digits
* `bin` · `oct` · `hex` — integer-base output; locale and precision are ignored

;`precision` semantics by notation:
* `auto` · `scientific` · `engineering` → significant digits (default 6) — ISO 80000-1
* `fixed` → decimal places after the point (default 6)

;`notation="auto"` — thresholds (ISO 80000-1: > 4 significant figures → scientific):
* `|x| < 10⁻³` or `|x| ≥ 10⁴` → scientific notation
* Otherwise → fixed (decimal) notation
* Example: `9 999` → `9 999` (fixed); `10 000` → `1 × 10⁴` (scientific); `0.001` → `1 × 10⁻³` (scientific)

---

!! Numeric input — accepted formats

|!Format |!Example |
|Decimal point |`3.14` |
|Thousands space |`1 000 000` |
|Thousands comma (EN style) |`1,000,000` |
|Scientific notation |`5e9` · `1.5e-3` · `2.5e+6` |

⚠️ Do ''not'' write `5 * e9` — that means 5 times the undefined symbol `e9`.

