---

!! Reserved identifiers ⚠️

|!Name |!Value |!Risk |
| `e` |Euler's number, 2.718… |shadows the constant for the whole expression |
| `i` |imaginary unit, √−1 |complex results become plain numbers |

Use `euler`, `base`, `idx`, `imag`, or any other name instead.

---

!! Complex numbers

* `2 + 3i` → `2 + 3i` (displayed normally)
* `(2 + 3i) * (1 - i)` → `5 + i`
* `abs(3 + 4i)` → `5` (modulus)
* `sqrt(-1)` → `i`

---

!! Units

;Arithmetic with units
* `5 m + 50 cm` → `5.5 m`
* `9.81 m/s^2 * 80 kg` → `784.8 N`
* `12 N / m^2` → `12 Pa`

;Conversion (`to`)
* `12 cm to mm` → `120 mm`
* `12.7 cm to inch` → `5 inch`
* `12 m/s to km/h` → `43.2 km/h`
* `100 degF to degC` → `37.778 °C`
* `460 V * 20 A * 30 days to kWh` → `6624 kWh`

;Extract numeric value in target unit
* `number(5cm, mm)` → `50`

---

!! Formula rendering — `show="formula"` / `show="full"`

KaTeX by default when the plugin is installed; pretty-printed plain text otherwise or when `output="text"`.

<$codeblock code="""<$calc show="formula">(a+b)/c</$calc>
<$calc show="full" mode="block">sqrt(x^2 + 1)</$calc>"""/>

;KaTeX automatic conversions:
* `sqrt(x^2+1)` → `\sqrt{x^{2}+1}`
* `(a+b)/c` → `\frac{a+b}{c}`
* `pi` → `\pi`

;Plain text pretty-print conversions (`output="text"`):
* `pi` → `π`   `e` → `ℯ`   `Infinity` → `∞`
* `*` → `·`
* `x^2` → `x²`   `x^23` → `x²³`
* `sqrt(…)` → `√(…)`   `cbrt(…)` → `∛(…)`
* `factorial(n)` → `n!`
* `log10(x)` → `log₁₀(x)`   `log2(x)` → `log₂(x)`
* Numbers with 4+ digits get NNBSP as thousands separator: `1000000` → `1 000 000`; decimal separator follows `locale`.
* Scientific exponents use Unicode superscripts: `10⁻⁶` not `10^-6`.

⚠️ `show="formula"` does not evaluate — `notation`, `precision`, `calcPrec`, and `scope` are ignored.
⚠️ `mode="block"` is now honoured for `output="text"` (centres result in a block `<div>`).

---

!! Variable scope — `scope` attribute

;Tiddler mode (one `name: expression` per line)
<$codeblock code="""<$calc scope="MyVars">pi * r^2</$calc>"""/>

```
r: 5
h: 10
vol: pi * r^2 * h
```

Later lines can reference earlier variables. Values must use EN notation.

;Inline mode (object literal, evaluated by mathjs — sandboxed)
<$codeblock code="""<$calc scope="{r: 3, h: 10}">pi * r^2 * h</$calc>"""/>

* Keys: `r2` ✓ `my_var` ✓ `_x` ✓ — `2r` ✗ `my-var` ✗
* No quotes on keys — `{a:1}` not `{"a":1}`
* Values: EN notation (decimal point), pairs separated by commas
* `math.unit(5 cm)` auto-quoted — no need for inner quotes
* With `calcPrec="64/128/256"`, all literals are automatically BigNumber
* Values may be mathjs expressions: `{angle: pi/4}`

---

!! Precision and performance ⚠️

Default is `float` (IEEE 754, ~16 digits). BigNumber only needed for specific cases.

;When BigNumber is actually needed:
|!Situation |!Example |!float result |!BigNumber |
|Catastrophic cancellation |`1e13 + 1.23456789 - 1e13` |`1.234375` ❌ |`1.23456789` ✅ |
|Subtraction residual |`0.3 - 0.1 - 0.1 - 0.1` |`-2.78e-17` ❌ |`0` ✅ |
|Integer > 2^53 |`9007199254740993` |`9007199254740992` ❌ |`9007199254740993` ✅ |

;Performance (V8/Node.js):
|!`calcPrec` |!µs/eval arithmetic |!µs/eval `sin`/`cos` |!Widgets before 16 ms jank |
| `float` (default) |~13 µs |~14 µs |>1 000 ✅ |
| `64` |~66 µs |~925 µs |~240 arith. / ~17 trig |
| `128` |~169 µs |~1 957 µs |~94 arith. / ~8 trig |
| `256` |~89 µs |~5 346 µs |~180 arith. / ~3 trig |

;Hard limit — trig at high `calcPrec`:
`sin` `cos` `tan` `asin` `acos` `atan` `sinh` `cosh` throw `[DecimalError] Precision limit exceeded` at precision ≥ 510. The widget caps options at `256`.

;LRU cache:
500 entries — each unique expression evaluated only once per tiddler change.

;`calcPrec` vs `precision`:
`calcPrec` → internal accuracy (invisible). `precision` → visible digits. Raising `calcPrec` does ''not'' add visible digits.

---

!! Error messages

All expression errors are debounced 200 ms (suppresses flicker while typing).

|!Situation |!Message |!Silenceable |
|Unclosed parenthesis |exact position reported |Yes |
|Unknown identifier |`Unknown function: "sqt" — did you mean "sqrt"?` |Yes |
|Division by zero |`Result is +∞ — division by zero or overflow` |Yes |
|Trig at calcPrec ≥ 510 |`[DecimalError] Precision limit exceeded` |Yes |
|Invalid scope |`Problem with the scope attribute` |Yes |
